{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1160,"text":"Two weeks ago,"},{"time":2560,"text":"I was sitting at the kitchen table\nwith my wife Katya,"},{"time":7960,"text":"and we were talking about\nwhat I was going to talk about today."},{"time":13040,"text":"We have an 11-year-old son;\nhis name is Lincoln."},{"time":15720,"text":"He was sitting at the same table,\ndoing his math homework."},{"time":20240,"text":"And during a pause\nin my conversation with Katya,"},{"time":23840,"text":"I looked over at Lincoln"},{"time":25600,"text":"and I was suddenly thunderstruck"},{"time":29640,"text":"by a recollection of a client of mine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":33080,"text":"My client was a guy named Will."},{"time":35880,"text":"He was from North Texas."},{"time":38920,"text":"He never knew his father very well,"},{"time":40680,"text":"because his father left his mom\nwhile she was pregnant with him."},{"time":46520,"text":"And so, he was destined\nto be raised by a single mom,"},{"time":50720,"text":"which might have been all right"},{"time":52221,"text":"except that this particular single mom\nwas a paranoid schizophrenic,"},{"time":57840,"text":"and when Will was five years old,"},{"time":60800,"text":"she tried to kill him\nwith a butcher knife."}]},{"cues":[{"time":64280,"text":"She was taken away by authorities\nand placed in a psychiatric hospital,"},{"time":69360,"text":"and so for the next several years\nWill lived with his older brother,"},{"time":72640,"text":"until he committed suicide\nby shooting himself through the heart."},{"time":77080,"text":"And after that Will bounced around\nfrom one family member to another,"},{"time":81920,"text":"until, by the time he was nine years old,\nhe was essentially living on his own."}]},{"cues":[{"time":86960,"text":"That morning that I was sitting\nwith Katya and Lincoln,"},{"time":89600,"text":"I looked at my son, and I realized\nthat when my client, Will, was his age,"},{"time":97480,"text":"he'd been living by himself for two years."},{"time":101640,"text":"Will eventually joined a gang"},{"time":104000,"text":"and committed a number\nof very serious crimes,"},{"time":108400,"text":"including, most seriously of all,"},{"time":111760,"text":"a horrible, tragic murder."},{"time":115440,"text":"And Will was ultimately executed\nas punishment for that crime."}]},{"cues":[{"time":122600,"text":"But I don't want to talk today\nabout the morality of capital punishment."},{"time":128479,"text":"I certainly think that my client\nshouldn't have been executed,"},{"time":132360,"text":"but what I would like to do today instead"},{"time":135280,"text":"is talk about the death penalty\nin a way I've never done before,"},{"time":140360,"text":"in a way that is\nentirely noncontroversial."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145600,"text":"I think that's possible,"},{"time":147280,"text":"because there is a corner\nof the death penalty debate --"},{"time":151520,"text":"maybe the most important corner --"},{"time":153840,"text":"where everybody agrees,"},{"time":156600,"text":"where the most ardent\ndeath penalty supporters"},{"time":160880,"text":"and the most vociferous abolitionists\nare on exactly the same page."},{"time":167520,"text":"That's the corner I want to explore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":171240,"text":"Before I do that, though,\nI want to spend a couple of minutes"},{"time":174160,"text":"telling you how\na death penalty case unfolds,"},{"time":177760,"text":"and then I want to tell you two lessons"},{"time":179960,"text":"that I have learned over the last 20 years\nas a death penalty lawyer"},{"time":185040,"text":"from watching well more\nthan a hundred cases unfold in this way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":190680,"text":"You can think of a death penalty case\nas a story that has four chapters."},{"time":195960,"text":"The first chapter of every case\nis exactly the same, and it is tragic."},{"time":201040,"text":"It begins with the murder\nof an innocent human being,"},{"time":204960,"text":"and it's followed by a trial"},{"time":206720,"text":"where the murderer\nis convicted and sent to death row,"},{"time":209720,"text":"and that death sentence is ultimately\nupheld by the state appellate court."}]},{"cues":[{"time":214640,"text":"The second chapter consists\nof a complicated legal proceeding"},{"time":217560,"text":"known as a state habeas corpus appeal."},{"time":221200,"text":"The third chapter is an even\nmore complicated legal proceeding"},{"time":224160,"text":"known as a federal\nhabeas corpus proceeding."},{"time":226680,"text":"And the fourth chapter is one\nwhere a variety of things can happen."},{"time":230520,"text":"The lawyers might file\na clemency petition,"},{"time":233040,"text":"they might initiate\neven more complex litigation,"},{"time":235560,"text":"or they might not do anything at all."},{"time":238040,"text":"But that fourth chapter\nalways ends with an execution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":242960,"text":"When I started representing\ndeath row inmates more than 20 years ago,"},{"time":247120,"text":"people on death row\ndid not have a right to a lawyer"},{"time":249800,"text":"in either the second\nor the fourth chapter of this story."},{"time":253480,"text":"They were on their own."},{"time":255120,"text":"In fact, it wasn't until the late 1980s"},{"time":257560,"text":"that they acquired a right to a lawyer\nduring the third chapter of the story."},{"time":262440,"text":"So what all of these death row inmates\nhad to do was rely on volunteer lawyers"},{"time":268000,"text":"to handle their legal proceedings."},{"time":270360,"text":"The problem is that there were\nway more guys on death row"},{"time":273760,"text":"than there were lawyers"},{"time":275040,"text":"who had both the interest\nand the expertise to work on these cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278800,"text":"And so inevitably,"},{"time":280484,"text":"lawyers drifted to cases\nthat were already in chapter four --"},{"time":284440,"text":"that makes sense, of course."},{"time":285840,"text":"Those are the cases that are most urgent;"},{"time":287840,"text":"those are the guys\nwho are closest to being executed."},{"time":290348,"text":"Some of these lawyers were successful;"},{"time":292189,"text":"they managed to get\nnew trials for their clients."},{"time":294520,"text":"Others of them managed\nto extend the lives of their clients,"},{"time":297400,"text":"sometimes by years, sometimes by months."}]},{"cues":[{"time":300320,"text":"But the one thing that didn't happen"},{"time":302760,"text":"was that there was never\na serious and sustained decline"},{"time":306720,"text":"in the number of annual\nexecutions in Texas."},{"time":309520,"text":"In fact, as you can see from this graph,"},{"time":311480,"text":"from the time that the Texas\nexecution apparatus got efficient"},{"time":314880,"text":"in the mid- to late 1990s,"},{"time":316960,"text":"there have only been a couple of years"},{"time":318794,"text":"where the number of annual\nexecutions dipped below 20."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322920,"text":"In a typical year in Texas,"},{"time":324960,"text":"we're averaging about two people a month."},{"time":328880,"text":"In some years in Texas,\nwe've executed close to 40 people,"},{"time":333080,"text":"and this number has never significantly\ndeclined over the last 15 years."},{"time":338120,"text":"And yet, at the same time\nthat we continue to execute"},{"time":341520,"text":"about the same number\nof people every year,"},{"time":343800,"text":"the number of people who we're\nsentencing to death on an annual basis"},{"time":347680,"text":"has dropped rather steeply."}]},{"cues":[{"time":349960,"text":"So we have this paradox,"},{"time":351920,"text":"which is that the number\nof annual executions has remained high"},{"time":356160,"text":"but the number of new\ndeath sentences has gone down."},{"time":360200,"text":"Why is that?"},{"time":361600,"text":"It can't be attributed\nto a decline in the murder rate,"},{"time":364480,"text":"because the murder\nrate has not declined nearly so steeply"},{"time":368080,"text":"as the red line\non that graph has gone down."},{"time":371080,"text":"What has happened instead"},{"time":373440,"text":"is that juries have started to sentence\nmore and more people to prison"},{"time":377760,"text":"for the rest of their lives\nwithout the possibility of parole,"},{"time":381080,"text":"rather than sending them\nto the execution chamber."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384880,"text":"Why has that happened?"},{"time":386560,"text":"It hasn't happened\nbecause of a dissolution"},{"time":389720,"text":"of popular support for the death penalty."},{"time":391920,"text":"Death penalty opponents\ntake great solace in the fact"},{"time":394800,"text":"that death penalty support in Texas\nis at an all-time low."},{"time":399280,"text":"Do you know what all-time low\nin Texas means?"},{"time":401440,"text":"It means that it's in the low 60 percent."},{"time":403680,"text":"Now, that's really good\ncompared to the mid-1980s,"},{"time":406480,"text":"when it was in excess of 80 percent,"},{"time":409160,"text":"but we can't explain\nthe decline in death sentences"},{"time":412080,"text":"and the affinity for life\nwithout the possibility of parole"},{"time":415320,"text":"by an erosion of support\nfor the death penalty,"},{"time":417720,"text":"because people still support\nthe death penalty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":419960,"text":"What's happened to cause this phenomenon?"},{"time":423320,"text":"What's happened is that lawyers\nwho represent death row inmates"},{"time":428000,"text":"have shifted their focus\nto earlier and earlier chapters"},{"time":431600,"text":"of the death penalty story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433560,"text":"So 25 years ago,\nthey focused on chapter four."},{"time":436920,"text":"And they went from\nchapter four 25 years ago"},{"time":439280,"text":"to chapter three in the late 1980s."},{"time":442280,"text":"And they went from chapter three\nin the late 1980s"},{"time":444800,"text":"to chapter two in the mid-1990s."},{"time":447240,"text":"And beginning in the mid- to late 1990s,"},{"time":449320,"text":"they began to focus\non chapter one of the story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":452320,"text":"Now, you might think\nthat this decline in death sentences"},{"time":455240,"text":"and the increase\nin the number of life sentences"},{"time":457520,"text":"is a good thing or a bad thing."},{"time":459040,"text":"I don't want to have a conversation\nabout that today."},{"time":461560,"text":"All that I want to tell you\nis that the reason that this has happened"},{"time":464840,"text":"is because death penalty lawyers\nhave understood"},{"time":467840,"text":"that the earlier you intervene in a case,"},{"time":470627,"text":"the greater the likelihood that\nyou're going to save your client's life."},{"time":474520,"text":"That's the first thing I've learned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476440,"text":"Here's the second thing I learned:"},{"time":478560,"text":"My client Will was\nnot the exception to the rule;"},{"time":483160,"text":"he was the rule."},{"time":486200,"text":"I sometimes say, if you tell me\nthe name of a death row inmate --"},{"time":489800,"text":"doesn't matter what state he's in,"},{"time":491480,"text":"doesn't matter\nif I've ever met him before --"},{"time":493640,"text":"I'll write his biography for you."},{"time":496040,"text":"And eight out of 10 times,"},{"time":498440,"text":"the details of that biography\nwill be more or less accurate."}]},{"cues":[{"time":503080,"text":"And the reason for that is that 80 percent\nof the people on death row"},{"time":506760,"text":"are people who came from the same sort\nof dysfunctional family that Will did."},{"time":511000,"text":"Eighty percent of the people on death row"},{"time":513200,"text":"are people who had exposure\nto the juvenile justice system."},{"time":518039,"text":"That's the second lesson\nthat I've learned."}]},{"cues":[{"time":521320,"text":"Now we're right on the cusp of that corner"},{"time":525280,"text":"where everybody's going to agree."},{"time":528240,"text":"People in this room might disagree"},{"time":530040,"text":"about whether Will\nshould have been executed,"},{"time":532720,"text":"but I think everybody would agree"},{"time":535080,"text":"that the best possible\nversion of his story"},{"time":538720,"text":"would be a story\nwhere no murder ever occurs."},{"time":544480,"text":"How do we do that?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":546520,"text":"When our son Lincoln was working\non that math problem two weeks ago,"},{"time":551280,"text":"it was a big, gnarly problem."},{"time":553600,"text":"And he was learning how,\nwhen you have a big old gnarly problem,"},{"time":557080,"text":"sometimes the solution\nis to slice it into smaller problems."},{"time":561040,"text":"That's what we do for most problems --"},{"time":562920,"text":"in math, in physics,\neven in social policy --"},{"time":565080,"text":"we slice them into smaller,\nmore manageable problems."},{"time":568400,"text":"But every once in a while,\nas Dwight Eisenhower said,"},{"time":572160,"text":"the way you solve a problem\nis to make it bigger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":577560,"text":"The way we solve this problem"},{"time":579960,"text":"is to make the issue\nof the death penalty bigger."},{"time":583800,"text":"We have to say, all right."},{"time":586160,"text":"We have these four chapters\nof a death penalty story,"},{"time":590920,"text":"but what happens before that story begins?"},{"time":595520,"text":"How can we intervene\nin the life of a murderer"},{"time":599400,"text":"before he's a murderer?"},{"time":602240,"text":"What options do we have\nto nudge that person off of the path"},{"time":608000,"text":"that is going to lead\nto a result that everybody --"},{"time":611400,"text":"death penalty supporters\nand death penalty opponents --"},{"time":614200,"text":"still think is a bad result:"},{"time":617360,"text":"the murder of an innocent human being?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":622240,"text":"You know, sometimes people say\nthat something isn't rocket science."},{"time":627840,"text":"And by that, what they mean\nis rocket science is really complicated"},{"time":631160,"text":"and this problem that we're\ntalking about now is really simple."},{"time":634680,"text":"Well that's rocket science;"},{"time":636120,"text":"that's the mathematical expression\nfor the thrust created by a rocket."},{"time":642040,"text":"What we're talking about today\nis just as complicated."},{"time":646480,"text":"What we're talking about today\nis also rocket science."}]},{"cues":[{"time":651800,"text":"My client Will and 80 percent\nof the people on death row"},{"time":656800,"text":"had five chapters in their lives"},{"time":659800,"text":"that came before the four chapters\nof the death penalty story."},{"time":664040,"text":"I think of these five chapters\nas points of intervention,"},{"time":667720,"text":"places in their lives"},{"time":669400,"text":"when our society\ncould've intervened in their lives"},{"time":673000,"text":"and nudged them off of the path\nthat they were on"},{"time":676000,"text":"that created a consequence that we all --"},{"time":678640,"text":"death penalty supporters\nor death penalty opponents --"},{"time":681560,"text":"say was a bad result."}]},{"cues":[{"time":683840,"text":"Now, during each of these five chapters:"},{"time":686520,"text":"when his mother was pregnant with him;"},{"time":688480,"text":"in his early childhood years;"},{"time":690560,"text":"when he was in elementary school;"},{"time":692160,"text":"when he was in middle school\nand then high school;"},{"time":694526,"text":"and when he was\nin the juvenile justice system --"},{"time":696842,"text":"during each of those five chapters,"},{"time":698541,"text":"there were a wide variety of things\nthat society could have done."},{"time":701620,"text":"In fact, if we just imagine"},{"time":703240,"text":"that there are five\ndifferent modes of intervention,"},{"time":705960,"text":"the way that society could intervene\nin each of those five chapters,"},{"time":710200,"text":"and we could mix and match them\nany way we want,"},{"time":712480,"text":"there are 3,000 -- more than 3,000 --\npossible strategies"},{"time":716520,"text":"that we could embrace"},{"time":717840,"text":"in order to nudge kids like Will\noff of the path that they're on."}]},{"cues":[{"time":723160,"text":"So I'm not standing here today\nwith the solution."},{"time":727080,"text":"But the fact that we\nstill have a lot to learn,"},{"time":731520,"text":"that doesn't mean\nthat we don't know a lot already."},{"time":735040,"text":"We know from experience in other states"},{"time":737840,"text":"that there are a wide variety\nof modes of intervention"},{"time":741640,"text":"that we could be using in Texas,"},{"time":743280,"text":"and in every other state\nthat isn't using them,"},{"time":746080,"text":"in order to prevent a consequence\nthat we all agree is bad."}]},{"cues":[{"time":750400,"text":"I'll just mention a few."},{"time":752960,"text":"I won't talk today\nabout reforming the legal system."},{"time":756960,"text":"That's probably a topic"},{"time":758240,"text":"that is best reserved\nfor a room full of lawyers and judges."},{"time":761720,"text":"Instead, let me talk\nabout a couple of modes of intervention"},{"time":765720,"text":"that we can all help accomplish,"},{"time":767840,"text":"because they are modes of intervention\nthat will come about"},{"time":770626,"text":"when legislators and policymakers,\nwhen taxpayers and citizens,"},{"time":774720,"text":"agree that that's\nwhat we ought to be doing"},{"time":776800,"text":"and that's how we ought\nto be spending our money."}]},{"cues":[{"time":779160,"text":"We could be providing early childhood care"},{"time":782200,"text":"for economically disadvantaged\nand otherwise troubled kids,"},{"time":787240,"text":"and we could be doing it for free."},{"time":789760,"text":"And we could be nudging kids like Will\noff of the path that we're on."},{"time":793960,"text":"There are other states\nthat do that, but we don't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797600,"text":"We could be providing special schools,"},{"time":800200,"text":"at both the high school level\nand the middle school level,"},{"time":803000,"text":"but even in K-5,"},{"time":805160,"text":"that target economically\nand otherwise disadvantaged kids,"},{"time":808160,"text":"and particularly kids who have had\nexposure to the juvenile justice system."},{"time":812640,"text":"There are a handful\nof states that do that;"},{"time":814800,"text":"Texas doesn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816920,"text":"There's one other thing we can be doing --\nwell, there are a bunch of other things --"},{"time":820960,"text":"there's one other thing\nthat I'm going to mention,"},{"time":823320,"text":"and this is going to be the only\ncontroversial thing that I say today."},{"time":826630,"text":"We could be intervening\nmuch more aggressively"},{"time":830000,"text":"into dangerously dysfunctional homes,"},{"time":833200,"text":"and getting kids out of them"},{"time":835160,"text":"before their moms pick up butcher knives\nand threaten to kill them."},{"time":840600,"text":"If we're going to do that,\nwe need a place to put them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":844560,"text":"Even if we do all of those things,"},{"time":846240,"text":"some kids are going\nto fall through the cracks"},{"time":848440,"text":"and they're going to end up\nin that last chapter"},{"time":850720,"text":"before the murder story begins,"},{"time":852280,"text":"they're going to end up\nin the juvenile justice system."},{"time":854920,"text":"And even if that happens,\nit's not yet too late."},{"time":858600,"text":"There's still time to nudge them,"},{"time":861400,"text":"if we think about nudging them\nrather than just punishing them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":865400,"text":"There are two professors\nin the Northeast --"},{"time":867520,"text":"one at Yale and one at Maryland --"},{"time":869200,"text":"they set up a school\nthat is attached to a juvenile prison."},{"time":873880,"text":"And the kids are in prison,\nbut they go to school"},{"time":876240,"text":"from eight in the morning\nuntil four in the afternoon."},{"time":878840,"text":"Now, it was logistically difficult."},{"time":880560,"text":"They had to recruit teachers\nwho wanted to teach inside a prison,"},{"time":883840,"text":"they had to establish strict separation"},{"time":885722,"text":"between the people who work at the school\nand the prison authorities,"},{"time":889000,"text":"and most dauntingly of all,"},{"time":890360,"text":"they needed to invent a new curriculum\nbecause you know what?"},{"time":893280,"text":"People don't come into and out of prison\non a semester basis."}]},{"cues":[{"time":896370,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":898160,"text":"But they did all those things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":901240,"text":"Now, what do all of these things\nhave in common?"},{"time":904000,"text":"What all of these things have in common\nis that they cost money."},{"time":910320,"text":"Some of the people in the room\nmight be old enough"},{"time":912720,"text":"to remember the guy\non the old oil filter commercial."},{"time":917160,"text":"He used to say, \"Well, you can pay me now\nor you can pay me later.\""},{"time":924040,"text":"What we're doing\nin the death penalty system"},{"time":928600,"text":"is we're paying later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":931880,"text":"But the thing is\nthat for every 15,000 dollars"},{"time":935800,"text":"that we spend intervening"},{"time":938000,"text":"in the lives of economically\nand otherwise disadvantaged kids"},{"time":941760,"text":"in those earlier chapters,"},{"time":943080,"text":"we save 80,000 dollars\nin crime-related costs down the road."},{"time":947800,"text":"Even if you don't agree that\nthere's a moral imperative that we do it,"},{"time":954360,"text":"it just makes economic sense."}]},{"cues":[{"time":958200,"text":"I want to tell you about the last\nconversation that I had with Will."},{"time":962320,"text":"It was the day that\nhe was going to be executed,"},{"time":967680,"text":"and we were just talking."},{"time":970120,"text":"There was nothing left to do in his case."},{"time":973280,"text":"And we were talking about his life."},{"time":975760,"text":"And he was talking first about his dad,\nwho he hardly knew, who had died,"},{"time":980360,"text":"and then about his mom,\nwho he did know, who was still alive."}]},{"cues":[{"time":985880,"text":"And I said to him,"},{"time":988600,"text":"\"I know the story."},{"time":990600,"text":"I've read the records."},{"time":992520,"text":"I know that she tried to kill you.\""},{"time":994920,"text":"I said, \"But I've always wondered"},{"time":996560,"text":"whether you really\nactually remember that.\""},{"time":999560,"text":"I said, \"I don't remember anything\nfrom when I was five years old."},{"time":1003600,"text":"Maybe you just remember\nsomebody telling you.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1006400,"text":"And he looked at me and he leaned forward,"},{"time":1008800,"text":"and he said, \"Professor,\" --"},{"time":1010200,"text":"he'd known me for 12 years,\nhe still called me Professor."},{"time":1012920,"text":"He said, \"Professor,\nI don't mean any disrespect by this,"},{"time":1015960,"text":"but when your mama\npicks up a butcher knife"},{"time":1018440,"text":"that looks bigger than you are,"},{"time":1020840,"text":"and chases you through the house\nscreaming she's going to kill you,"},{"time":1024640,"text":"and you have to lock yourself\nin the bathroom"},{"time":1026960,"text":"and lean against the door"},{"time":1028240,"text":"and holler for help\nuntil the police get there,\""},{"time":1032000,"text":"he looked at me and he said,"},{"time":1033960,"text":"\"that's something you don't forget.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1037480,"text":"I hope there's one thing\nyou all won't forget:"},{"time":1040200,"text":"In between the time\nyou arrived here this morning"},{"time":1042560,"text":"and the time we break for lunch,"},{"time":1044160,"text":"there are going to be\nfour homicides in the United States."},{"time":1047640,"text":"We're going to devote\nenormous social resources"},{"time":1050840,"text":"to punishing the people\nwho commit those crimes,"},{"time":1053120,"text":"and that's appropriate"},{"time":1054360,"text":"because we should punish\npeople who do bad things."},{"time":1056760,"text":"But three of those crimes are preventable."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059880,"text":"If we make the picture bigger"},{"time":1063160,"text":"and devote our attention\nto the earlier chapters,"},{"time":1067360,"text":"then we're never going\nto write the first sentence"},{"time":1070840,"text":"that begins the death penalty story."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1073680,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1074920,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}